ExecDesc.value: Apple Quicktime RTSP URL Handler Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: This threat simulates a client requesting a Quicktime video stream, and the server replying with a maliciously constructed qtl file. This file will cause a buffer overflow in the Quicktime player by a vulnerability in the RTSP URL handler. The transport of the qtl file is done via HTTP, which generally runs on port 80.
